Example 19

For a scale of $1 : 500\,000$, find the actual length represented by a drawn length of 15 cm.

actual length $=$ drawn length $\times 500\,000$ {scale factor $500\,000$}

$\therefore$ actual length $= 15$ cm $\times 500\,000$
$= 7\,500\,000$ cm
$= (7\,500\,000 \div 100)$ m {1 m $= 100$ cm}
$= 75\,000$ m
$= (75\,000 \div 1000)$ km {1 km $= 1000$ m}

$\therefore$ actual length $= 75$ km
